article.headline: Davis has 21 as Delaware knocks off William & Mary 69-58
article.description: — Jyare Davis' 21 points helped Delaware defeat William & Mary 69-58 on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Davis has 21 as Delaware knocks off William & Mary 69-58
article.story: NEWARK, Del. -- — Jyare Davis' 21 points helped Delaware defeat William & Mary 69-58 on Saturday night. Davis also had 10 rebounds for the Blue Hens (16-9, 8-4 Coastal Athletic Association). Niels Lane added 16 points while going 7 of 13 and 2 of 3 from the free throw line, and he also had five rebounds. Christian Ray was 5 of 10 shooting and 3 of 3 from the free throw line to finish with 13 points, while adding 15 rebounds. Trey Moss led the way for the Tribe (8-17, 3-9) with 18 points. Chase Lowe added 17 points and eight rebounds for William & Mary. Gabe Dorsey also had 12 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
